    "name": "Question 21 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "What is the potential difference between a 3µF capacitor plates if the stored energy is 2.0 x 10⁻³J?",
      "type": "subJective"
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "36.5V"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Capacitor Energy to Voltage</h3><p>Using the energy formula:</p><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'><strong>U = ½CV² ⇒ V = √(2U/C)</strong></p><h4 style='color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 15px;'>Calculation:</h4><p>V = √(2 × 2.0×10⁻³J / 3×10⁻⁶F) = √(4/3 × 10³) ≈ <strong>36.5V</strong></p></div>"
    },
