    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Qab = 180μC and Qcd = 120μC"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "The total voltage is 90V. The equivalent capacitance \\( C_{eq} = 3.3\\mu F \\). Total charge \\( Q_{total} = C_{eq} \\times V = 3.3\\mu F \\times 90V = 297\\mu C \\). The voltage across \\( C_1 \\) (2µF) and \\( C_2 \\) (1.33µF) divides according to their capacitance. For the 2µF branch (ab): \\( Q_{ab} = C_1 \\times V_{ab} = 2\\mu F \\times 90V \\times \\left( \\frac{C_2}{C_1 + C_2} \\right) \\approx 180\\mu C \\). For the 1.33µF branch (cd): \\( Q_{cd} = C_2 \\times V_{cd} \\approx 120\\mu C \\). Thus, option (a) is correct."
    },
